Section 1:
1 L.D. 239
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Secretary of the Senate.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 105, L.D. 239, “An Act to Allow Retail
10 Pharmacies to Operate Remote Dispensing Sites in Rural Areas”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 32 MRSA §13751, sub-§2, ¶A-1 is enacted to read:
14 A-1. Remote dispensing site;
15 Sec. 2. Maine Board of Pharmacy to adopt rules. No later than June 30, 2026,
16 as authorized by the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 32, section 13751, subsection 2,
17 paragraph A-1, the Maine Board of Pharmacy shall adopt rules to establish the criteria that
18 a remote dispensing site must meet to qualify for licensure. The rules must, at a minimum,
19 require a demonstration that the geographic area in which the remote dispensing site is to
20 be located lacks adequate access to retail pharmacy services for the general public;
21 authorize a licensed pharmacist to provide supervision, drug regimen review and patient
22 counseling through telehealth services under Title 32, chapter 117, subchapter 15; set
23 minimum staffing levels for pharmacy technicians at the remote dispensing site; and
24 establish procedures for record keeping, security and surveillance. The operation of a
25 remote dispensing site by a retail pharmacy is not permitted until rules are adopted by the
26 board pursuant to Title 32, section 13751, subsection 3 and this section. Rules adopted
27 pursuant to this section are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375,
28 subchapter 2-A.'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment authorizes a remote dispensing site
3333 as a new category of license for a pharmacy and requires the Maine Board of Pharmacy to
3344 adopt rules to establish criteria that a remote dispensing site must meet to qualify for a
Page 1 - 132LR0374(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 105, L.D. 239
315 license. The amendment requires the Maine Board of Pharmacy to adopt rules no later than
326 June 30, 2026.
337 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
348 (See attached)
